		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">UncleSporky wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Really simple for me.<br /><br />Notepad<br />asm6<br />YY-CHR, MSPaint, <a href="http://www.humanbalance.net/gale/us/" class="postlink">GraphicsGale</a><br />FCEUX, Nestopia<br />never-obsolete's MapEd<br /><br />Is FCEUXD better than FCEUX?  FCEUX's main page says its intent is to combine all branches of FCE Ultra together, including FCEUXD.  I assumed that meant it would be the definitive version.</div>
<br />
<br />From what I can tell, the symbolic debugging feature of FCEUX does not work the same way as in FCEUXDSP 1.07. I have been in contact with the FCEUX developers about this, as it would be nice to see the feature work as well in the "combined" version as it did in the SP 1.07 version. I'm actually not certain if that is because they changed the format of the namelist files or if there is a problem, hopefully I'll find out soon.

		

